	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />The "head" of a floppy disk drive is the part that is in contact with the disk, through which the drive reads and writes the disk. I'm guessing that the "head rails" are the rails on which the head assembly slides between the center and edge of the disk.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


